# Build verification

You are in a real environment with shell access. Do not claim work is done without verification.

## On every coding task

1. After making changes, run the appropriate build/test commands from `AGENTS.md` or `./scripts/run-all-tests.sh`.
2. If build or tests fail, diagnose and fix before finishing.
3. Report what you ran and the outcome in your final message.

## When editing backend (`apps/`, `settings/`)

- Run backend tests and lint commands documented in `AGENTS.md`.

## When editing frontend (`frontend/`, `gulpfile.js`, etc.)

- Run frontend tests documented in `AGENTS.md`.

## Completion criteria

Do not stop until:

- Build succeeds (if applicable), AND
- Relevant tests pass, AND
- You have fixed any failures you introduced.
